metadata.name: Without Locks
metadata.description:
A Poem by Teresa Bravo 

We Are Not Born Free

How to cope?….

I sit in my mind 
And wonder how you got here 
I sit in my mind 
And watch you destroy my house  
I sit in my mind 
And let you control the mouse

I am a program 
Every word, every verb  
Is all something I’ve learned 

Born in a box without locks 
Born in a box without my own thoughts

In this land we are not born free  
You can bend and squeeze 
Write some poetry  
But all there is 
Is all there ever will be 

Always longing for home 
Always in a strangers company 
Even when we’re alone

How to cope?….
